explains: adj. 高性能的；精力充沛的，强有力的；马力大的

sentences.en: I had a very high-powered job in publishing.
sentences.cn: 我曾在出版业有一份位高权重的工作。

sentences.en: They are in the workplace, doing the high-powered jobs the graduates want, but cannot get.
sentences.cn: 他们在工作场所，做着毕业生想要却得不到的高强度工作。

sentences.en: The key to the Greek world lay in its high-powered ships; the key to Roman power lay in its marching legions.
sentences.cn: 希腊世界的关键是其强大的船队，而罗马帝国的关键则是它的步兵团。
